               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-192" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-192" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-192" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390812-name-192" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker, and live in Sun-court, Milton-street. I had some materials for making shoes, and some lasts belonging to William Hickson, and two pairs of uppers and other things of John Arthur Mason—the prisoner lodged in the same room with me—these things were kept there—I missed them on the 6th of August—the pri<lb></lb>soner went out in the evening of the 5th of August, and kept out till four o'clock next morning—these things are mine—I gave the prisoner two pairs of boots to make which belonged to Mason—he had no business to take them from my room, but to make them there, and deliver them to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390812-name-193" type="witnessName">
